      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until the squash is tender – this is your <strong>roasted butternut squash</strong></p>",
