    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped onion </strong>and<strong> garlic </strong>to the pot and cook for 3-4 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Once softened, add 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [40g] </span><strong>flour </strong>and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste coats the onion – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p>",
