    {
      "instruction": "<p>Gradually whisk in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> and the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong> to the roux, a little at a time, and cook for 4-5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p><p>Once done, add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>grated cheese</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>harissa paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) – this is your <strong>harissa</strong> <strong>béchamel sauce</strong></p>",
